@page "/label-interactive-demo"
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<PageTitle>Label ID in Interactive Mode</PageTitle>

<h1>Label <code>id</code> Attribute in Interactive Mode</h1>

<p>In Preview 2, the <code>id</code> attribute for input components is correctly generated in interactive render mode, enabling proper label/input association.</p>

<p>Inspect the rendered HTML to verify that each <code>&lt;input&gt;</code> has a generated <code>id</code> attribute matching the <code>&lt;label&gt;</code>'s <code>for</code> attribute.</p>

<EditForm Model="contact" FormName="label-id-form">
    <div class="mb-3">
        <Label For="() => contact.FirstName" class="form-label" />
        <InputText @bind-Value="contact.FirstName" class="form-control" />
    </div>
    <div class="mb-3">
        <Label For="() => contact.LastName" class="form-label" />
        <InputText @bind-Value="contact.LastName" class="form-control" />
    </div>
    <div class="mb-3">
        <Label For="() => contact.Email" class="form-label" />
        <InputText @bind-Value="contact.Email" class="form-control" />
    </div>
    <div class="mb-3">
        <Label For="() => contact.Age" class="form-label" />
        <InputNumber @bind-Value="contact.Age" class="form-control" />
    </div>
</EditForm>

<h2>What to verify</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Open browser DevTools and inspect the form elements</li>
    <li>Each <code>&lt;label&gt;</code> should have a <code>for</code> attribute</li>
    <li>Each <code>&lt;input&gt;</code> should have a matching <code>id</code> attribute</li>
    <li>This works because Preview 2 generates <code>id</code> independently of <code>name</code>, which is empty in interactive mode</li>
</ul>

@code {
    private ContactModel contact = new();

    public class ContactModel
    {
        [Display(Name = "First Name")]
        public string FirstName { get; set; } = "";

        [Display(Name = "Last Name")]
        public string LastName { get; set; } = "";

        [Display(Name = "Email Address")]
        public string Email { get; set; } = "";

        [Display(Name = "Age")]
        public int Age { get; set; }
    }
}
